findings.recommendation:
Add an explicit CSRF decision to Decision 5 (or as Decision 11). The SecurityConfig bean must call `.csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())` because this is a stateless REST API using token/header-based auth (not cookies). Document that when a frontend-integrated SSR flow with cookies is added in a later epic, CSRF must be re-evaluated. Example SecurityConfig skeleton:

```java
@Bean
public SecurityWebFilterChain securityWebFilterChain(ServerHttpSecurity http) {
    return http
        .csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())  // stateless REST API, no cookie auth
        .authorizeExchange(exchanges -> exchanges
            .pathMatchers("/health").permitAll()
            .anyExchange().authenticated()
        )
        .build();
}
```
